1
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:52,420
I already informed the Yuan. Our Goryeo soldiers will be crossing the Yalu River.

2
00:00:55,270 --> 00:00:58,680
Let's conquer Liaodong.

3
00:01:00,130 --> 00:01:01,950
Choi Yeong

4
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:06,680
is going to conquer Liaodong.

5
00:01:17,210 --> 00:01:21,650
Conquering Liaodong? It's impossible.

6
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:23,340
That can't happen.

7
00:01:23,340 --> 00:01:28,610
Every citizen of Goryeo has dreamed of conquering Liaodong.
(Sam Bong: Jeong Do Jeon)

8
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:31,760
The previous king was like that, even I was like that.

9
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,670
General Choi Yeong is probably like that too.

10
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:39,390
But didn't you say that you will do it in the future once you have raised the military power?
(Nam Eun)

11
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:44,390
An expedition when it's too much to even protect (the country)?
(Lee Bang Won)

12
00:01:44,390 --> 00:01:46,330
This is crazy.

13
00:01:46,330 --> 00:01:49,920
Just what are you saying?

14
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:54,120
Are you telling me to go on an expedition war in Liaodong?

15
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,410
That's right.

16
00:01:56,410 --> 00:01:59,650
His Highness and I are set on this.

17
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:08,910
No matter how I think about it, it's impossible.

18
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:13,480
If all the soldiers get drafted, then what will we do about this year's farming?

19
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:18,180
The military provisions are the same. What are we going to do when the first wheat harvest hasn't come yet?
(Moo Hyul)

20
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:22,530
Yes. Even during the first Liaodong expedition done by General Lee Seong Gye,

21
00:02:22,530 --> 00:02:28,240
all the wars that have been won still failed because of the lack of military provisions. Military troops were discharged in the fall season.

22
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:33,660
Then, in the fall... Please push it to fall.

23
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:39,100
After the harvest when there is an abundance of provisions for the army.
(Lee Seong Gye)

24
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:44,630
It has to be right now when 150,000 of Ming's soldiers are away at Great Yuan.

25
00:02:44,630 --> 00:02:47,330
What about the military provisions?

26
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:51,360
Say that we seize Liadong. Will there be enough supplies for 50,000 soldiers?

27
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:55,120
For now, take possession of Liaodong and provisions will be obtained on site.
(Choi Yeong)

28
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:59,310
The military's march will be hard, and the glue on the bows will melt.

29
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:01,750
And a contagious disease will take over the army.

30
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:03,650
Isn't that the same for the Ming?

31
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:08,170
They are in their home town and it's a military expedition for us.

32
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:16,670
Yes, yes. I heard your words well. General Lee's words make sense as well.

33
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:20,210
However,
(King U; 32nd ruler of Goryeo.)1

34
00:03:20,210 --> 00:03:25,320
Because of the Ming's unfair requests, the people are outraged as well.

35
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:27,790
If we fight with the same heart right now,

36
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:31,650
won't we be able to stop the tedious submission we've been forced into?

37
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:36,990
So, please follow my intentions, General Lee.

38
00:03:38,210 --> 00:03:43,470
General Lee, the King is asking you a question. Give him an answer.

39
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:45,400
Your Majesty.

40
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:53,200
This... cannot happen.

41
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,900
What?

42
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:05,990
I, Lee Seong Gye, am fearlessly speaking

43
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:10,640
with my head bowed down to you, Your Majesty.

44
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:18,110
Above all, it does not make sense for a small country to strike back at a bigger country.

45
00:04:18,110 --> 00:04:19,340
What?!

46
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:25,370
No matter what the outcome is, General Lee will receive tremendous damage.

47
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:27,870
Even if he wins?

48
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:32,850
Even if we win, we will lose half of the army.

49
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:35,510
No, even a half will be a relief.

50
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:39,780
Also, if we win we will be stuck in Liaodong.

51
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:44,230
That's correct. Liaodong is a land that is harder to defend than to overtake.

52
00:04:44,230 --> 00:04:48,070
Truthfully, the war will not end in any circumstances.

53
00:04:48,070 --> 00:04:52,110
Yes, unless we are trying to conquer the Chinese continent.

54
00:04:52,110 --> 00:04:57,010
General Lee will be the Ming's enemy and will be harassed for his entire life.

55
00:04:57,010 --> 00:05:02,020
Is that what General Choi was aiming for?

56
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:07,160
No, for General Choi Young it's only a strong belief he has.

57
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:11,690
Therefore, there would be no compromise at all.

58
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:14,320
What kind of nonsense are you talking about?!

59
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:18,280
A small country cannot attack a bigger country?

60
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:25,350
Although we are smaller to the Ming, we are the great Goryeo that has received vigor from Goguryeo.

61
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:30,710
We are the descendants of the Goguryeo that made the Sui and Tang countries, that unified the continent, fear them.

62
00:05:30,710 --> 00:05:34,760
When did Goguryeo conquer the Sui country?

63
00:05:41,790 --> 00:05:46,890
When did Goguryeo conquer the Tang country?

64
00:05:46,890 --> 00:05:51,080
To that big country, Goguryeo's spirit and vigor

65
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:55,090
will not surrender even a foot's distance of the country.

66
00:05:55,090 --> 00:05:59,130
Isn't this just putting the people in misery through a thoughtless conquest?

67
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:00,850
What?!

68
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:07,820
General.

69
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:14,980
Then are you saying that I am a king that put his people in misery with my thoughtless conquest?

70
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:20,620
Your Majesty, if the Ming do take over the northwest part of Goryeo,

71
00:06:20,620 --> 00:06:28,080
I, like Yang Man Choon and Eul Ji Moon, with my life will defeat the enemies.
(Yang and Eul-great generals that stopped the Sui and Tang country)

72
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:32,210
- But the conquest of Liadong...
- This man still!

73
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:35,710
Your Majesty, please calm down.

74
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:44,860
General Lee, how is a general who has never lost showing such a weak side?

75
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:49,190
I have not won all my fights.

76
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:52,600
What do you mean? You have never lost.

77
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:58,270
At the year 1370. Yes, I have conquered Liadong.

78
00:06:58,270 --> 00:07:00,820
We crossed the Yalu river and from Pasabo

79
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:05,120
to Yoyang Haengsung, we won all our fights.

80
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:11,110
But, what happened after the conquest?

81
00:07:11,110 --> 00:07:14,650
Because of the cold in Liaodong, we ran out of provisions and the supplies stopped coming over.

82
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:17,120
We had to make an absurd retreat.

83
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:22,800
Therefore, there were only 60 men who died in the war, but

84
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:26,920
while retreating there were more than four thousand men who died from hunger.

85
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:32,410
Men who should have gone home to their mothers as decorated heroes after winning the war,

86
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:36,230
I had to give them back as thousands of corpses.

87
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:41,110
How can that be considered a victory?

88
00:07:43,970 --> 00:07:48,220
For a great achievement, there has to be sacrifice.

89
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:52,730
Do not think of the soldiers who will be sacrificed in the Liaodong conquest.

90
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:57,870
Think of the many more descendants who will live on after we conquer Liaodong.

91
00:07:57,870 --> 00:08:03,230
There is truly no greed in General Choi's heart, but

92
00:08:03,230 --> 00:08:08,630
he also has no concern for the people. He has no heart for

93
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,990
each and every soldier.

94
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:19,720
By this, Is my dream going to end?

95
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,760
If not...

96
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:33,300
By this, is this the beginning of a terrible disaster for the people?

97
00:08:35,810 --> 00:08:39,770
Finally, is this how a revolution is going to start?

98
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:09,730
Park Ui Joong was nominated to go to Ming as an envoy.

99
00:09:09,730 --> 00:09:13,340
There was also a message that an envoy from the Ming is coming to Gaegyeong right now.

100
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:16,960
You take care of it, but before that,

101
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,390
there is an important announcement.

102
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:27,110
Right now, the King of Ming, is insisting on

103
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:32,040
holding the authority over the Northern land of Cheollyeong.

104
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:39,700
Our Highness' decision is that he will not accept any disrespectful request from the Ming.

105
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:42,400
Therefore, from this point on, the Ming

106
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:46,570
will be declared Goryeo's enemy.

107
00:09:46,570 --> 00:09:49,340
Also, we are chastising the confident Ming,

108
00:09:49,340 --> 00:09:56,240
and in order to gain our sovereignty and status,

109
00:09:57,660 --> 00:10:01,890
we are going to conquer Liaodong.

110
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:05,390
- Wait, what?!
- What are you talking about, Lord?

111
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:07,480
You said an envoy is coming from the Ming!

112
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,540
- What kind of nonsense is this?! 
- What..

113
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:13,250
What do you mean about a war with the strong Ming country?

114
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:15,720
That is nonsense!

115
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:22,610
General! What is all this without any discussion in the Do Dang?

116
00:10:22,610 --> 00:10:26,180
Conquering Liaodong? A war?

117
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:30,780
Messages were already sent to the five cities, and soon there will be 50,000 soldiers gathering in Seogyeong (today's Pyung Yang).

118
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:33,800
How can you secretly make a national decision like this?

119
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:37,780
In any time or place, where would you find a war that has not been secretly prepared?

120
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:40,500
What about the provisions? What about all those military provisions?

121
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:44,120
We are going to use the money we took from Hong In Bang and Gil Tae Mi for the military.

122
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:48,240
What about the food supplies?
It's a war that is happening far away.

123
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,780
Yes, there is still a long time until the harvest.

124
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:53,980
If there is a shortage of food supplies, we can just get them on the spot.

125
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:59,440
We just have to quickly conquer the Liaodong fortress and then take care of the public sentiment.

126
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,960
On top of that, 50,000?

127
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:05,180
If you take all of the strong young men in the country,

128
00:11:05,180 --> 00:11:07,060
who is going to farm

129
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:08,840
and who is going to stop the Japanese pirates?

130
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:13,160
How dare you complain about His Majesty's orders?!

131
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:21,420
The preparations for conquering LIaodong have already been completed.

132
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:25,540
There will be not another discussion about this matter in the Do Dang again.

133
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:42,960
I mean, what kind of ruckus is this?

134
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,100
Truthfully, this doesn't make sense at all.

135
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:49,550
The saved food supplies will be gone even before the 50,000 soldiers reach Liaodong.

136
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:50,880
This cannot happen.

137
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:55,590
We'll quickly gather the Confucians and discuss this and send up a memorandum to the king.

138
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:59,960
If General Choi is not senile, how can he make a decision like this?

139
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:04,860
Hong In Bang and Gil Tae Mi's property is not even close to being enough for the military.

140
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:09,430
After that, who is he going to get more money from?

141
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:12,240
Well that, probably from the people.

142
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:15,940
Where do you think our possessions come from?

143
00:12:15,940 --> 00:12:17,700
This is not the time for us to be here like this.

144
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:20,540
Quickly send a message to Hap Ha Lee In Gyeom.

145
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:26,120
Aigo, what help can we receive from someone who lost his position?

146
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:29,760
General Choi's earlier threat to us

147
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,460
was not exaggerated.

148
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:34,760
Ah, aish...

149
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:41,180
I thought General Choi was someone who knew about war, so how can he do this?

150
00:12:41,180 --> 00:12:46,290
How can we take away 50,000 soldiers when the Japanese pirates are finally quieting down?

151
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:51,370
We will be stepped on by the Japanese pirates who have been saving their strength.

152
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:56,540
Even during King Gong Min, when there were less Japanese pirates, it was a conquest we gave up.

153
00:12:56,540 --> 00:13:01,720
But a conquest while we have Japanese pirates at our backs?

154
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:05,090
Older brother, this is too much.

155
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:10,960
Also, back then, Liaodong did not really have a true owner.

156
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:15,270
But now our opponent is the Ming. We cannot do this, Father.

157
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:20,240
I have already said everything I could.

158
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:28,240
But, a soldier has to take a command if it's given.

159
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:34,860
And you men and I are this country's soldiers.

160
00:13:40,610 --> 00:13:43,470
There is no words from Sam Bong yet?

161
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:46,890
No, not yet.

162
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:53,330
Do you know Tai Gong Wang Lu Shang?
(A strategist who met King Wen while wishing and then raised a country)

163
00:13:53,330 --> 00:14:00,280
Isn't he an angler? You think I do not know that you were imitating him these past days?

164
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:07,800
He is first man in history to change the king.

165
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:13,840
Twenty-five hundred years ago he was passing the time with his straight fishing hook,

166
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,840
even past his seventies.

167
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:18,130
So what?
(Lee Bang Ji)

168
00:14:18,130 --> 00:14:21,880
"Because of this war everything we have been preparing for has gone back to zero.

169
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:25,060
So now I am going to wait for the time."

170
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,620
Is it something like that?

171
00:14:27,620 --> 00:14:29,320
No.

172
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:34,170
The longer I hold this fishing rod,

173
00:14:34,170 --> 00:14:40,460
I only gain the thought that I am not even close to that angler.

174
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:49,620
But why did the angler use a straight fishing hook?

175
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:55,220
He said that a bent fishing hook only tricks the world.

176
00:14:55,220 --> 00:15:01,120
Then, how many did he catch with the straight fishing hook?

177
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,080
He probably could not catch any.

178
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:08,820
Even 2500 years ago or right now,

179
00:15:08,820 --> 00:15:14,140
isn't the outcome the same? You cannot catch anything with this.

180
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:19,140
Tell everyone to gather immediately.

181
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:36,570
So?

182
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:40,330
Our general's voice was loud and clear ,even outside the tent,

183
00:15:40,330 --> 00:15:42,850
that conquering Yo Dong cannot happen.

184
00:15:42,850 --> 00:15:45,840
It even seemed like His Majesty wielded his sword.

185
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:50,000
Oh, from outside I was like, "Do I have to go in?"

186
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,370
Oh, then it's a treason. What do I do?

187
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:55,310
Ah, our general... What to do?

188
00:15:55,310 --> 00:15:58,120
Uh, oh, uh... I was like that and

189
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:00,960
got ten years older.

190
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:07,860
Anyhow, our general's family's archery skills are amazing.

191
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:14,580
What about the teacher? Is he still at the fishing place?

192
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:17,490
Yes, it is already been five days.

193
00:16:17,490 --> 00:16:23,090
What the... Even if he loves fishing that much, how can he in a situation like this?

194
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:32,350
- Let's go.
- Pardon?

195
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:34,600
Call brother Nam Eun and Lee Shin Jeok for me as well.

196
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,680
Where are you going?

197
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,490
Yo. (added formal ending)

198
00:16:40,490 --> 00:16:42,760
The time is finally coming.

199
00:16:53,030 --> 00:16:56,060
We have all come from to your call.

200
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:58,950
Did you catch a lot of fish?

201
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:03,670
Bang Ji was saying that the angler seems like a crazy person.

202
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:12,860
So? Did you make up your mind?

203
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:17,390
I could not catch anything with a straight hook.

204
00:17:17,390 --> 00:17:21,710
In the end the angler could not gain anything from fishing.

205
00:17:21,710 --> 00:17:27,370
He got up from the fishing place and met the king and raised the country.

206
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:34,540
So are we carrying out our plan?

207
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:41,580
Yes, it's revolution.

208
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:53,640
You guys gather all our men and announce my words.

209
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,280
Yes.

210
00:17:55,280 --> 00:18:00,420
Boon Yi with all the messengers get ready for the things that will happen later on.

211
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:01,520
Yes.

212
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:08,380
Bang Won you make sure you bring General Lee Ji Ran and Bang Gwah in on this and move all the soldiers.

213
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:09,760
Yes, Teacher.

214
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:14,660
But, the result of this depends on General Lee.

215
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:18,900
In any situation, the general has to be determined.

216
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:22,320
Everyone be perfectly prepared.

217
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:26,340
Without General Lee's cooperation we are not taking a single action.

218
00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:27,410
Do you understand?

219
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:29,640
- Yes.
- Yes.

220
00:18:36,450 --> 00:18:38,810
This is what you mentioned.

221
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:44,510
I have gathered information on the people who can lead an army from General Lee's people.

222
00:18:44,510 --> 00:18:47,970
If you give this to Boon Yi, she will get their whereabouts.

223
00:18:47,970 --> 00:18:50,020
Yes.

224
00:18:50,020 --> 00:18:52,880
You will have to do the finishing.

225
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:53,950
Are you talking about Choi Young?

226
00:18:53,950 --> 00:18:58,020
In an situation l like this, talented soldiers will protect him.

227
00:18:58,020 --> 00:19:03,480
You will have the soldiers behind you so you surely have to catch him alive.

228
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,500
Please do not worry.

229
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:10,210
A revolution?

230
00:19:11,230 --> 00:19:14,660
So? What do you want me to do?

231
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:18,560
We''ll have to to catch General Choi and get the king's document

232
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:21,240
and stop the war.

233
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:30,080
If we attend this war, Ga Byeol Cho and father is definitely done for.

234
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,950
It's not only the older brother.

235
00:19:32,950 --> 00:19:36,670
This country, this country is going to done for.

236
00:19:36,670 --> 00:19:43,270
So the two of you have to move the soldiers in Ham Joo.

